  [1] =E2=80=9CCrypto solves this,=E2=80=9D some rapidly dwindling number o=
f readers are thinking. =E2=80=9CBlockchains solve the same problems that o=
ther digital services solve, but with better outcomes,=E2=80=9D writes Chri=
s Dixon. =E2=80=9CThey can connect people in social networks, while empower=
ing users over corporate interests. They can underpin marketplaces and paym=
ent systems that facilitate commerce, but with persistently lower take rate=
s. They can enable new forms of monetizable media, interoperable and immers=
ive digital worlds, and artificial intelligence services that compensate =
=E2=80=94 rather than cannibalize =E2=80=94 creators and communities.=E2=80=
=9D And when you find a blockchain-based social network whose users share i=
n its value, *and that is as popular as Reddit*, you let me know.


  [2] Nvidia was one of  10 cornerstone investors, and by market cap it was=
 one of the bigger ones; Nvidia disclosed that the cornerstone investors pu=
