rnerstone investors put in an average of $73.5 million each =E2=80=94 the $=
735 million total divided by 10 =E2=80=94 then it would be weird for Nvidia=
 to put in *less* than that average. If Nvidia bought $73.5 million of stoc=
k at the $51 IPO price, then by Dec. 29, 2023 =E2=80=94 the  measurement da=
te for Nvidia=E2=80=99s Form 13F obligations =E2=80=94 that stake would be =
worth about $108 million, since Arm=E2=80=99s stock had gone up to $75.145.=
 There are holes in that reasoning (=E2=80=9Cany of the Cornerstone Investo=
rs may determine to purchase more, fewer, or no ADSs in this offering, or t=
he underwriters may determine to sell more, fewer, or no ADSs to any of the=
 Cornerstone Investors,=E2=80=9D said Arm=E2=80=99s disclosure), but it=E2=
